    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3410252810" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3410252810" />
    <a title="Luís" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s"><img alt="Luís" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620236159p2/117399210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3410252810?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luís" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luís" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s">Luís</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/15731919-a-educa-o-sentimental">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=france-belgium-swiss">france-belgium-swiss</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3410252810" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16759261232950014224">Flaubert said of “L&apos;Education Sentimentale”: “I want to write the moral history of the men of my generation;“ sentimental ”would be more accurate. It is a book of love, of passion; but of desire such as &apos;it can exist, i.e. inactive &quot;. I find that this paragraph perfectly illustrates the book&apos;s idea, namely that through this story, Flaubert offers us a book of Passions, and who says Passions also says Suffering.<br/><br/>Indeed, the author sets up a wide range of characters, each more passionate than the o</span>
  <span id="freeText16759261232950014224" style="display:none">Flaubert said of “L'Education Sentimentale”: “I want to write the moral history of the men of my generation;“ sentimental ”would be more accurate. It is a book of love, of passion; but of desire such as 'it can exist, i.e. inactive ". I find that this paragraph perfectly illustrates the book's idea, namely that through this story, Flaubert offers us a book of Passions, and who says Passions also says Suffering.<br /><br />Indeed, the author sets up a wide range of characters, each more passionate than the other, and this by their actions or their ambitions: whether it is the fiery and sublime Passion between Frédéric Moreau and Mme Arnoux - but also carnal love with Rosanette, or interested with Mme Dambreuse, which nonetheless both remain passionate loves -, or that of Deslauriers for his career and glory, that of Arnoux for Money and Beauty, that of Pilgrim for Art ...<br />But, like the silent and impossible love between the hero and Madame Arnoux, we see that the search for the ideal and happiness by each individual is in vain. Moreover, in the last pages of the novel, Frédéric and Deslauriers dwell on their past and note their failure: "And they summed up their life. They both missed it, the one who had dreamed of love [ Frédéric], the one who dreamed of power [Deslauriers] "<br /><br />Not having heard, a priori, that praise on this novel by Flaubert, I opened this book with a lot of apprehensions and the fear of being bored during this reading ... But it does not. Is nothing in the end! Of course, there are many lengths, but despite that, I really enjoyed this read. Fans of Flaubert's style will certainly not be disappointed by "L 'Éducation Sentimentale".</span>
  <a data-text-id="16759261232950014224" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

